# TWSX — Inline Styles Utility

**Goal:** Convert Tailwind classes to React CSSProperties for inline styles.

**IMPORTANT:** TWSX does NOT support responsive modifiers (md:, lg:, xl:), pseudo-classes (:hover, :focus), or animations. Use `className` for those.

---

## Core Concept

```tsx
// ✅ Use className for responsive layouts
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6" />

// ✅ Use twsx() for simple inline styles
import { twsx } from '@/lib/twsx';
<div style={twsx('p-4 m-2 bg-primary')} />
```

---

## Usage Patterns

### Basic Inline Styles
```tsx
import { twsx } from '@/lib/twsx';

function MyComponent() {
  return (
    <div style={twsx('p-4 m-2 bg-primary text-primary-foreground')}>
      Content
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Conditional Styles (with spread)
```tsx
<div style={{
  ...twsx('p-4 rounded-lg'),
  ...(isActive ? twsx('bg-primary') : twsx('bg-secondary'))
}}>
  Content
</div>
```

### Module-Level Styles
```tsx
import { twsx } from '@/lib/twsx';

const styles = {
  card: twsx('p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm bg-card'),
  title: twsx('text-xl font-semibold text-foreground')
};

function Card({ title, children }) {
  return (
    <div style={styles.card}>
      <h2 style={styles.title}>{title}</h2>
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}
```

